Why Your Prompt Templates Aren't Working

People treat prompt engineering like memorizing recipe cards—plug in canned phrases and expect great results.

A stark black-and-white image captures a lone boxer seated in deep shadow, filling the frame with intensity and physical presence. The figure is positioned slightly off-center, leaning forward with shoulders hunched and arms drawn inward. One gloved fist rests prominently in the foreground, its rounded form catching a hard edge of light, while the other arm fades into darkness. The gloves appear worn, creased from repeated impact, suggesting long use rather than display.

The boxer’s upper body is bare, skin slick with sweat that reflects the light in sharp highlights across the chest, shoulders, and face. Muscles are defined but not posed, held in a state of readiness rather than performance. A tattoo is faintly visible on the upper arm, partially obscured by shadow. The lighting is severe and directional, carving the body out of darkness while leaving the surrounding space undefined.

The face is half-lit, half-consumed by shadow. One eye emerges clearly, focused and unwavering, staring outward with a mixture of exhaustion and resolve. The other side of the face dissolves into black, emphasizing imbalance and inner tension. Moisture beads along the brow and cheek, reinforcing the sense of heat, effort, and confinement.

The background offers no detail, no ropes, no ring, no crowd. It is an absence rather than a place, turning the moment inward. The atmosphere is heavy and compressed, as if sound itself has been removed. The image captures the space between action, where breath is counted, pain is assessed, and the next decision waits in silence.
